<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangzhou Links Up With Shanghai Stock Exchange </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1303022794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0146 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1303022794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 13 (XINHUA) -- The Guangzhou Nanfang 
Securities Exchange Center has been linked up with the Shanghai 
Stock Exchange in a network which will be put into operation on 
March 14. 
  The Shanghai Stock Exchange is currently linked with the 
securities markets in Fuzhou and Shenyang. It plans to link up 
with Tianjin and five other cities in the near future. 
  The Nanfang Securities Exchange Center has 64 members, among 
which 34 have started trading. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

