<H3> <TI>   Qingdao Foreign Trade Fair Opens in Shandong Province </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1203144394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1242 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1203144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Qingdao, March 12 (XINHUA) -- The 11th Qingdao 
Foreign Trade Fair opens today in Qingdao, a scenic coastal city 
in east China's Shandong Province, three months earlier than 
usual. 
  More than 600 overseas businessmen from Japan, Hong Kong, 
the 
United States, Germany, the Republic of Korea, Russia, Italy, 
Singapore and Taiwan attended the ceremony. 
  It is estimated that more than 3,000 overseas businessmen 
will attend the fair. 
  Shandong, one of the leading economic powers in China, held 
the first Qingdao Foreign Trade Fair in 1982. This year the 
local government advanced the date of the fair and cut short its 
duration from the usual 10 days to seven days. 
  A delegation from northwestern Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous 
Region is attending the fair. 

</TEXT>

