<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Commercial Enterprises Try Out Mergers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1303020494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0106 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1303020494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, March 13 (XINHUA) -- The commercial sector 
in east China's Zhejiang Province is stepping up efforts to 
generate more value from existing assets through the annexation 
of loss- making enterprises. 
  Commercial enterprises used to engage only in commodity 
sales. But this kind of resource distribution was often 
inefficient and failed to meet the demand in an increasingly 
competitive market. 
  Since 1992 such enterprises have been experimenting with 
annexing loss-making manufacturers and found that combining 
commerce with industry works to restore profitability. 
  Many commercial establishments with solid financial standing 
have opened their own factories, mostly through annexing 
inefficient industrial operations. 
  The assets flow in the commercial sector helps expansion of 
their businesses, creates a larger market share and brings in 
more business. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

