  [Text] Taipei, March 15 (CNA) -- Chang Feng-hsu, president 
of the Chinese Taipei Olympic Committee, will lobby for Taiwan's 
bid to host the 2002 Asian Games while at the executive board 
meeting of the Olympic Council of Asia. 
  The meeting, to be held March 26 and 27 in Bangkok, 
