<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Meets Opposition Party Delegate From Japan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1403140394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1328 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1403140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 14 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Chinese Communist Party (CPC), met here this afternoon with 
Japanese Diet member Susumu Nikaido, adviser to Japan's Liberal 
Democratic Party. 
  Jiang welcomed Nikaido and his party, saying that Nikaido, 
an 
old friend of the Chinese people, had made outstanding 
contributions in helping the former Japanese Prime Minister 
Kakuei Tanaka in 1972 realize the normalization of bilateral 
relations and the development of Sino-Japanese friendly 
relations. 
  Jiang said that since the normalization of bilateral 
relations, friendly cooperation between the two countries in all 
fields had made much progress and bilateral relations had 
entered a new stage. 
  He pointed out that China has long paid much attention to 
the 
development of a good-neighborly relationship with Japan, hoping 
that the two countries will continue to enhance understanding 
and strengthen cooperation so as to bring Sino-Japanese 
relations to a new height. 
  Jiang said: "I met with Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa last year in seattle and we are expecting Hosokawa to 
visit China." 
  Nikaido said that since relations between the two countries 
returned to normal in 1972, bilateral friendly relations and 
cooperation have been developing. 
  He said that although he was now aged 84, he would try to 
contribute to the further development of bilateral friendly 
relations. 
  President of the China-Japan Friendship Association Sun 
Pinghua and Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan took part in the 
meeting. 
  Nikaido and his party came here at the invitation of the 
China-Japan Friendship Association. 
  Before coming to Beijing, Nikaido attended a ceremony on 
March 12 to mark the completion of the Shanghai Baori 
High-Molecular Material Co., which is a joint venture between 
the Shanghai Metallurgical Construction Corporation and the 
Sanken Industry Co. of Japan. The joint venture is expected to 
produce heat-insulating and fire-proof materials. 

</TEXT>

