<H3> <TI>   Presidential Office Extends Welcome to Gorbachev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503142494 Taipei CNA in English 1320 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1503142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Bear Le] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, March 15 (CNA) -- The Presidential Office 
on Tuesday [15 March] said that it welcomes the coming visit 
here by Mikhail Gorbachev, the former president of the Soviet 
Union. 
  Presidential Office Deputy Secretary-general and Spokesman 
Raymond Tai said that Gorbachev is one of the most-respected 
figures in the world today, and that his visit shows the regard 
with which he holds Taiwan. 
  Tai said that the former Soviet [words indistinct] together 
with former United States President Ronald Reagan and former 
British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher, were the three world 
leaders that brought the Cold War to an end. 
  Gorbachev, who will be accompanied by his wife, Raisa, is 
scheduled to arrive in Taipei on Sunday for a five-day visit. 
He will meet President Li Teng-hui, Premier Lien Chan and other 
officials and deliver several public speeches during his stay 
here. 

</TEXT>

