<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Meets Canadian Entrepreneur 14 March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1403133594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1247 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1403133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 14 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice Premier 
Zou Jiahua met here today with Jacques Bougie, president and 
chief executive of Aluminum Canada (ALCAN). 
  Zou said that China's economy had developed fast since the 
country adopted its opening-up and reform policies in 1978, 
adding that entrepreneurs from Canada are welcome to invest here. 
  China follows two principles in its economic cooperation 
with 
foreign countries, the vice premier said. One is equality and 
mutual benefit. If the cooperation benefits only one side, it 
is doomed to fail. 
  The other is that it is in the long-term interests of both 
sides. Zou noted that the cooperation should take this into 
consideration. 
  He pointed out that China has rich resources and a huge 
market, adding that the future of the economic cooperation with 
China is promising. 
  Bougie briefed Zou on ALCAN's plan of conducting further 
economic cooperation with China, saying that he believed the 
aluminum industry in China would enjoy a bright future. 

</TEXT>

