<H3> <TI>   U.S. Extends Nuclear Test Moratorium </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503223894 Beijing XINHUA in English 2125 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1503223894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington, March 15 (XINHUA) -- The United States 
announced today that it would extend for one more year its 
moratorium on nuclear testing when it expires in September. 
  President Bill Clinton notified congressional leaders of the 
extension on Monday [14 March]. 
  Any resumption of nuclear weapons testing would have to be 
approved by Congress. 
  "The President will decide next year whether to extend the 
moratorium beyond September 1995," White House Spokeswoman Dee 
Dee Myers said. 
  The U.S. Congress has set a September 1996 target for an end 
to nuclear tests. 

</TEXT>

