<H3> <TI>   Southwest Airlines Sells 3 Boeings to U.S. Company </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1403141394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1343 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1403141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chongqing, March 14 (XINHUA) -- China Southwest 
Airlines based in Chongqing, in southwest China's Sichuan 
Province, recently sold three old Boeing 707 airliners to a 
Pacific Ocean Aviation Support Company from the United States. 
  They were sold for 2.55 million U.S. dollars. 
  The airliners have flown more than 25,000 hours on average 
and were taken out of service in August 1993. 
  The planes will be overhauled by China Southwest Airlines 
and 
be sent to the location appointed by the U.S. company before 
June 20 this year. 
  One of them will be dismantled for spare parts and the 
others 
will be converted for other uses after being repaired in Britain. 

</TEXT>

