<H3> <TI>   U.S. Sponsored Medical Forum Opens in Lhasa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0703084194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0812 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0703084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lhasa, March 7 (XINHUA) -- A forum on medical 
education sponsored by the China Medical Board of New York City 
in the United States opened Saturday [5 March] in Lhasa. 
  More than 70 medical workers from all over the Tibet 
Autonomous Region will be briefed on the modern medical 
examination system during the five-day forum. 
  Dr. Sawyer, chairman of the board, attended Saturday's 
opening ceremony. He is on his fifth trip to Lhasa. 
  The chairman said his board would help Tibet improve its 
medical education and examination system and train more medical 
professionals. 
  The board last year reached an agreement with authorities in 
Tibet to expand the regional medical school in Lhasa to a 
medical college. 
  It had already sponsored two medical forums in Lhasa. 

</TEXT>

