<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   NPC Presidium Holds Second Meeting 17 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703025594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0246 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703025594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 17 (XINHUA) -- The Presidium of the 
ongoing Second Session of the Eighth National People's Congress 
(NPC) held its second meeting here today in the Great Hall of 
the People. 
  The meeting passed a draft resolution on the government work 
report made by Premier Li Peng to the legislature. The 
resolution will be sent to NPC deputies for examination before 
being submitted to the NPC general session for a vote. 
  The Presidium meeting also heard and passed examination 
reports made by Liu Suinian, chairman of the NPC Financial and 
Economic Committee, on: implementation of the 1993 plan for 
national economic and social development, a draft 1994 plan for 
national economic and social development, implementation of the 
state budget for 1993 and a draft state budget for 1994. 
  The NPC Financial and Economic Committee, Liu said, believed 
that the guiding idea, principle and key points of the 1994 
national economic and social development plan are correct and 
that measures put forth therein are feasible. In the process of 
carrying out the national plan, he said, any partial adjustment 
of the plan has to be reported to the NPC Standing Committee for 
examination and approval. 
  On this year's budget plan, the committee maintains that its 
guiding principles for budgetary arrangements are correct, Liu 
said. 
  The principles, he said, provide for expenditures on key 
projects and undertakings that will promote national economic 
and social development. At the same time, the budget provides a 
necessary financial guarantee for the smooth progress of major 
reform measures and strengthened macroeconomic controls, he said. 
  The meeting also passed a draft list of candidates for by- 
election of members to the NPC Standing Committee to be handed 
over to the deputies for examination. 

</TEXT>

