<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Feature on Group Photo of Jiang Zemin, Others </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703103894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0922 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1703103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Feature by XINHUA correspondent Zou Aiguo (6760 1947 0948): </F>
"Spring Air in the Grand Meeting"] 
  [Text] Beijing, 8 Mar (XINHUA) -- On the afternoon of 8 
March, there were constant cheers and happy laughter at the 
Great Hall of the People. The Second Session of the National 
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference [CPPCC] would open soon. 
  Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, and other 
comrades left a reception room amid light-hearted music and went 
to the rostrum of the full session. The 10,000-man hall was 
lighted by ceiling lights, wall lights, and correspondents' 
flash bulbs. 
  Facing numerous cameras, General-Secretary Jiang Zemin 
pulled 
Li Peng, Qiao Shi, and Li Ruihuan together and happily said: 
"Come, let us have a group photo taken!" 
  Photographic correspondent rushed forward to photograph 
their 
smiling faces. 
  Earlier, a reception room in the rear of the main assembly 
hall was bustling with noise and excitement as a closed circuit 
TV was broadcasting the video recording of Li Ruihuan's visit to 
three countries in Southeast Asia. When Vice Chairman Wang 
Guangying saw Li Ruihuan coming into the room with a smiling 
face, he pointed at the TV and said: "Chairman Li, the TV is 
broadcasting you. You are the first person visiting abroad in 
the position of chairman of the CPPCC National Committee. It 
was very significant to developing foreign contacts by the 
CPPCC!" Li Ruihuan said repeatedly: "The achievements of the 
CPPCC all depend on your joint efforts." 
  At a reception room, Ye Xuanping and Wang Zhaoguo, vice 
chairmen of the CPPCC National Committee, were greeting party 
and state leaders who came to extend their greetings. Ye 
Xuanping held talks with some responsible persons of democratic 
parties, and later extended his greetings to Ann Tse-kai, Henry 
Fok Ying-tung, and Ma Man-kei, vice chairmen of the CPPCC 
National Committee who were elected from Hong Kong and Macao 
regions; Wang Zhaoguo asked for advice from Wang Hanbin, vice 
chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's 
Congress, concerning legal matters in contacts between the two 
sides of the Taiwan Strait. 
  Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, and other comrades entered 
the reception room to express their congratulations to Li 
Ruihuan on the opening of the CPPCC session. Li Ruihuan 
introduced Zhu Xun, minister of geology and mineral resources 
and first deputy secretary general of the Second Session of the 
Eighth CPPCC National Committee, to comrades Jiang Zemin, Li 
Peng, and Qiao Shi, saying: "This is our newly elected member 
and Minister of Geology and Mineral Resources Zhu Xun." Jiang 
Zemin shook hands with him and said: "We knew each other long 
ago." Li Peng said to Zhu Xun: "The CPPCC can do a lot of 
things. You must continue your efforts under the leadership of 
Comrade Li Ruihuan." 
  The preparatory bell sounded, and Zhu Xun requested those 
leading comrades to take their seats at the rostrum. When 
General-Secretary Jiang Zemin saw Ye Xuanping wearing a 
feather-padded coat, he asked the latter: "You will make a 
report at the plenary meeting wearing just this?" Ye Xuanping 
took off the feather-padded coat and said smilingly: "I wear a 
western coat underneath!" Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, and 
other comrades all laughed. 

</TEXT>

