<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Party Calls for Better Use of Foreign Funds </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703083794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0807 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703083794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 17 (XINHUA) -- Zheng Shouyi, leader 
of a democratic party in China, today proposed ways to better 
attract and utilize foreign funds and improve the management of 
foreign-funded enterprises. 
  After reviewing achievements in the introduction of foreign 
funds in recent years, Zheng Shouyi, vice-chairman of the 
Central Committee of the China Zhi Gong Party (Public Interest 
Party), said in a speech that attention should be paid to the 
solution of problems in the introduction of foreign funds. 
  "Governments at all levels should draw up long-term plans 
for 
the introduction and use of foreign funds in a bid to improve 
their macro-management in this regard," he told a meeting of the 
current session of the National Committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference today. 
  They should also formulate policies and principles 
concerning 
the use of foreign funds, in line with specific economic 
conditions of their respective regions, he said. 
  It is also necessary to formulate regulations and policies 
to 
encourage foreign investors, and examine both annual and 
long-term plans for the introduction of foreign funds, he added. 
  He proposed setting up managerial departments to coordinate 
efforts to solve major problems in using such funds. 
  In the future, it is necessary to attract investments from 
multi- national corporations and international consortiums, and 
encourage them to invest in energy, transportation and other 
infrastructure projects, he said. 
  They should also be encouraged to undertake major projects 
to 
upgrade technology in existing large and medium-sized 
state-owned enterprises, he added. 
  "At present, the amount of foreign investment in public 
health, education and culture is very small. I think we should 
make breakthroughs in these areas," he said. 
  Zheng Shouyi called for efforts to perfect China's legal 
system, noting that legislative measures must be compatible with 
internationally accepted practices. 
  Foreign-funded enterprises inside China must be treated as 
Chinese legal entities, he said, adding that both Chinese- and 
foreign-funded enterprises should be treated equally. 
  Furthermore, it is imperative to tighten supervision over 
tax 
payments by foreign-funded companies, accurately evaluate 
foreign assets and protect the legitimate rights and interests 
of workers in these companies, he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

