<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army NPC Deputy Urges Upgrading PLA Combat Ability </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1703105494 Beijing JIEFANGJUN BAO in Chinese 12 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK1703105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing JIEFANGJUN BAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by reporter Li Yin (2621 0692): "At an NPC Session </F>
Panel Forum, Deputy Zhang Zhen Speaks About `Three 
Modernizations' Army Construction and the Comprehensive 
Enhancement of the Troops' Combat Capability"] 
  [Text] Beijing, 11 Mar (JIEFANGJUN BAO)--Zhang Zhen, Army 
deputy to the National People's Congress [NPC], today stressed 
during a panel discussion on Premier Li Peng's government work 
report that, under the new situation of reform and opening up, 
the People's Liberation Army [PLA] has an important duty in the 
areas of safeguarding the country's security and maintaining 
social stability. He called for strengthening our Army's 
revolutionized, modernized, and regularized construction; for 
the overall improvement of the Army's combat ability; and for 
the provision of a strong and forceful security guarantee for 
reform, opening up, and modernization. 
  In his speech, Zhang Zhen first reflected on the 
world-renowned great achievements in reform, opening up, and 
modernization in our country since the Third Plenary Session of 
the 11th CPC Central Committee. With vivid and meticulous facts 
and figures, he detailed the positive situation and vitality in 
which our country enjoys political stability, economic 
development, ethnic unity, and social progress. He thought 
that, regarding the great achievements in reform and opening up 
over the past 15 years, education and propaganda must be carried 
out properly, to further unify thinking, arouse fighting spirit, 
and enhance soldiers' morale. 
  NPC deputy Zhang Zhen said that the most basic reason 
enabling our country to make the great achievements is because 
we have upheld the party's basic line and have followed the road 
of socialism with Chinese characteristics. Practice has proven 
that this is the correct road. Comrade Deng Xiaoping has 
integrated the basic principle of Marxism with China's actual 
conditions, has established the theory of building socialism 
with Chinese characteristics, and has led us to realize the 
second historical leap. Zhang Zhen also said: There will still 
be various difficulties on the road ahead, but I believe that, 
under the guidance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics and under the strong and 
forceful leadership of the CPC Central Committee which has 
Comrade Jiang Zemin as the core, and with the strength and 
experience that we have acquired in the course of reform and 
opening up for more than a decade, and by the common effort of 
the people throughout the country, we are fully confident that 
we can win a new victory in reform and construction. 
  In discussing army building, NPC deputy Zhang Zhen happily 
said that, under the new situation of reform and opening up, the 
entire Army has vigorously strengthened ideological and 
political work, and the Army's party spirit building, clean 
government building, and spiritual civilization construction 
have scored good results. A great enthusiasm for military 
drilling has emerged throughout the Army, which has drilled hard 
for the ability to fight, and military exercises have witnessed 
a good situation which has rarely been seen in the past. In the 
area of logistics, comrades throughout the Army have developed 
the good tradition of building the Army diligently and 
economically; the logistics departments of various levels have 
worked hard to increase efficiency in the use of funds; and 
soldiers have enthusiastically engaged in agricultural and 
sideline productions, making new progress. The building of the 
national defense reserve strength has also scored marked 
results, and militia and reserve units have played an important 
role in building the economy and safeguarding social stability. 
After reflecting on the achievements in army building over the 
past year, Zhang Zhen said that this has fully indicated that 
our Army is firm politically, is resolute in listening to the 
party's words, and is completely trustworthy to the party and 
the people. 
  Zhang Zhen stressed that strengthening national defense, 
resisting aggression, protecting the motherland, and 
safeguarding the peaceful environment in which people work is 
the sacred duty entrusted to our Army by the constitution. 
Under the new situation of reform and opening up, the PLA has 
an important duty in the areas of safeguarding the country's 
security and maintaining social stability. Only by building a 
strong Army which is under the absolute leadership of the party 
and is loyal to the country and people can we maintain our 
country's security and stability and ensure a smooth process in 
reform, opening up, and modernization. 
  Zhang Zhen pointed out that, in order to properly build the 
Army, we must first seriously learn from Volume 3 of the 
Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping and must use Comrade 
Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics, as well as his idea of army building in the new 
period, to arm the minds of the officers and men throughout the 
Army. Only by so doing can we further enhance 
self-consciousness for implementing the party's basic line and 
maintain our Army's high degree of stability, centralism, and 
unity. Zhang Zhen also mentioned the need to expedite the 
process of forumulating national defense legislation and use 
legal means to strengthen national defense and army building. 
In this area, we must abide by the laws and regulations 
promulgated by the NPC and the government and must implement 
them resolutely. 
  Finally, Zhang Zhen also discussed with the deputies the 
problems of vigorously enhancing the sense of national defense 
among the whole people, actively supporting economic development 
in the frontier regions inhabited by minority nationalities, and 
giving play to the role of the militia and reserve units in 
maintaining law and order and social stability. 

</TEXT>

