<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Discusses Coal Production in Shanxi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703083194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0808 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 17 (XINHUA) -- China's main energy 
supply will depend on Shanxi Province for a considerably long 
period of time, Premier Li Peng said here today. 
  Joining deputies from Shanxi Province in a discussion during 
the current session of the National People's Congress, Li said 
that Shanxi has played and will continue to play an important 
role in the national economic development. 
  He noted that Shanxi supplies over 200 million tons of coal 
to other parts of China each year. 
  Coal mines run by townships and villages produce over half 
of 
the provincial coal output. The small coal mines have made 
contributions to the nation. "It is necessary to support small 
coal mines, accelerate their technical upgrading, strengthen 
their safe production and turn them into modernized or 
semi-modernized enterprises," he said. 
  On difficulties of state-owned enterprises, he said that 
solving problems of major state-owned enterprises is a vital but 
difficult issue in the current reform. The central authorities 
have decided to make continuous investigations in and study on 
this issue, which cannot be solved in one or two years or by 
adopting merely the joint-stock system. The invigoration of 
state-owned enterprises will depend mainly on technical progress 
and the production of marketable goods. 
  He also talked about building water conservancy projects to 
solve water shortages in Shanxi and about assisting the 
province's poor areas to develop their economies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
