<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fifth Meeting of National CPPCC Standing Committee Opens </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703095494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0900 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1703095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Sun Yong (1327 0516) and Zhu Dongju (2612 0392 </F>
5468) ] 
  [Text] Beijing, 1 Mar (XINHUA) -- The fifth meeting of the 
Standing Committee of the Eighth National Committee of the 
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC] 
opened this morning at the CPPCC auditorium. 
  It was presided over by CPPCC National Committee Chairman Li 
Ruihuan. 
  Members of the Standing Committee first examined and passed 
the agenda and schedule of the current Standing Committee 
meeting. According to the agenda, the meeting will examine and 
approve the Standing Committee's work report and the person to 
deliver the report at the Second Session of the Eighth National 
CPPCC Committee; discuss the "Report on the Work of the 
Government" (draft for soliciting opinions); examine and approve 
the "CPPCC Constitution (Draft Revision)"; hear and discuss a 
report by Comrade Wei Jianxing, secretary of the Central 
Discipline Inspection Commission, on the current situation of 
the anticorruption struggle; and examine and approve the 
namelists of the additional members to be elected to the Second 
Session of the Eighth National CPPCC Committee and the members 
to be elected to replace members of the Second Session. 
  At the meeting, Zhu Zuolin, deputy secretary general of the 
National CPPCC Committee, made an explanation on the agenda 
(draft) and schedule (draft) of the Second Session of the Eighth 
National CPPCC Committee. Chen Jinyu, deputy secretary general 
of the National CPPCC Committee, made an explanation on the 
drafting of the work report (draft) of the Eighth National CPPCC 
Committee Standing Committee. Lu Zhichao, deputy secretary 
general of the National CPPCC Committee, made an explanation on 
the "CPPCC Constitution (Draft Revision)." National CPPCC 
Committee Vice Chairman Wang Zhaoguo made an explanation on the 
namelists (draft) of the additional members to be elected to the 
Second Session of the Eighth National CPPCC Committee and the 
members to be elected to replace members of the Second Session. 
  In his speech, Li Ruihuan hoped that, during the session of 
the current meeting, Standing Committee members will seriously 
examine the aforementioned drafts, freely express their 
opinions, and submit the drafts to the current Standing 
Committee meeting or the Second Session of the Eighth National 
CPPCC Committee for examination and approval. 
  In November 1993 National CPPCC Committee member Shi Jiuyong 
was jointly elected a judge of the International Court for a 
nine-year term by the UN General Assembly and the UN Security 
Council. To abide by and to implement relevant stipulations of 
the International Court's rules, he tenendered his resignation 
as National CPPCC Committee member. National CPPCC Committee 
member Qian Qing tendered his resignation as member of the 
National CPPCC Committee's Foreign Affairs Committee for health 
reasons. After examination, the 10th chairmanship meeting has 
approved their requests to resign. The above was reported to the 
Standing Committee for the record. 
  The meeting examined and approved a decision on approving 
Comrade Song Demin's resignation as secretary general of the 
National CPPCC Committee for health reasons. 
  Because Liu Hanzhen supported and took part in fraudulent 
activities of "seeking treasures [zhao bao (2109 1405)" and 
"presenting treasures [xian bao (3759 1405)," and because Ma 
Liesun committed serious crimes, the meeting examined the cases 
and approved a decision on annulling Liu Hanzhen's and Ma 
Liesun's credentials as members of the Eighth National CPPCC 
Committee and its Standing Committee. 
  Those attending today's meeting included National CPPCC 
Committee Vice Chairmen Ye Xuanping, Wu Xueqian, Yang Rudai, 
Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme, Hong Xuezhi, Zhao Puchu, Qian Weichang, Hu 
Sheng, Qian Zhengying, Su Buqing, Ding Guangxun, Dong Yinchu, Su 
Fuling, and Ann Tse Kai. 

</TEXT>

