<H3> <TI>   State Council Issues Decree on Teaching Achievement Awards </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703024094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0221 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703024094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 17 (XINHUA) -- The State Council, 
China's highest governing body, has issued its 151st decree, on 
the implementation of regulations on rewarding people for 
teaching achievements. 
  The 16-article regulations, which was signed by Chinese 
Premier Li Peng and made known today, will reward collective 
units and individuals. The aim is to encourage more teachers to 
go in for research in education and improve concrete teaching 
activities. 
  The awards are divided into four grades, special and first, 
second and third classes, and the winners will be presented with 
certificates and medals as well as monetary awards. 
  All schools and universities, academic bodies and other 
social organizations, as well as teachers and other individuals 
can apply for prizes for teaching achievements in accordance 
with the stipulations stated in the regulations. 

</TEXT>

