<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dissident Suffers Heart Attack While Under House Arrest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1703031294 Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO in Chinese 17 Mar 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> HK1703031294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dispatch by LIEN HO PAO New York-based special </F>
correspondent Tseng Hui-yen (2582 1979 3601): "Ding Zilin and 
Her Husband, Cosigners of Human Rights Appeal, Placed Under 
House Arrest"] 
  [Text] New York, 16 Mar (LIEN HO PAO) -- Ding Zilin [0002 
1311 7207], professor at the People's University of China, and 
her spouse, Jiang Peikun [5592 1014 0981] -- two of the "seven 
gentlemen" who signed the human rights appeal in Beijing -- are 
still under house arrest. Personnel from the State Security 
Ministry, the National People's Congress Security Department, 
and the Family Dependents Commission keep a 24-hour watch in 
front of their house, and all who come to see them will be 
questioned and warned. This serious interference in her normal 
life has caused Ding Zilin to have a heart attack. Even when 
she went to the hospital for treatment, she was "accompanied" by 
some persons. 
  Several of her students who are studying in the United 
States 
have called this newspaper or faxed messages to us saying they 
were concerned about Ding Zilin's condition. At the same time, 
the Humanitarian Rescue Work Committee of the Autonomous 
Federation of Chinese Students and Scholars in America has urged 
the mainland authorities to lift the unlawful house arrest of 
Ding Zilin and her spouse immediately, on the grounds of 
humanitarianism, and to provide a good medical environment and 
treatment conditions for Ding Zilin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

