<H3> <TI>   WHO Designates Urban Health Development Center in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703103794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1010 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 17 (XINHUA) -- The World Health 
Organization (WHO) has recently designated the Dongcheng 
District Health Bureau of Beijing as the WHO collaborative 
center for urban health development. 
  S. T. Han, a regional director of WHO, unveiled a plaque for 
the center here today. 
  According to an official from the center, this collaborative 
center is aimed at enhancing the development of urban health 
care. It will study and report health problems caused by rapid 
urbanization and improve health care services, lifestyles and 
public policies for urban health development. 
  The center will also provide technical information and 
training for national and foreign professionals and support 
WHO's project activities in urban health development, said the 
official. 

</TEXT>

