<H3> <TI>   Sino-U.S. Safety Control Technology Seminar Held </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803073994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0707 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1803073994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 18 (XINHUA) -- More than 200 Chinese 
and U.S. scientists and engineers met here today for a two-day 
seminar on safety control technology. 
  Senior researchers from Triconex of the U.S., a leading 
international research and manufacturing firm in tripled 
fault-tolerant technology, said that they will co-operate with 
their Chinese counterparts in developing and introducing 
advanced safety and control systems for use in key Chinese 
industries. 
  Fault-tolerant technology, a by-product of the U.S. space 
industry, provides critical safety control for the nuclear, 
chemical, electric utility, aerospace, petrochemicals and other 
industries. 
  William Barkovitz, president of Triconex, said that this 
year 
his firm is planning to form a number of joint ventures in 
safety and control technology with Chinese industries. 

