<H3> <TI>   DPRK Official in Geneva Denounces U.S. Talks Cancellation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1803132694 Beijing China Radio International in Korean 
1100 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1803132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing China Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] (Han Sang-u), deputy chief of the DPRK mission in 
the UN Headquarters in Geneva, yesterday denounced the United 
States for having unilaterally canceled the DPRK-U.S. high-level 
talks and hindered the thorough resolution of the nuclear issue 
on the Korean peninsula. (Han Sang-u) stated that the attitudes 
of the United States and the International Atomic Energy Agency 
[IAEA] had complicated this matter and that it was difficult to 
predict their consequences. 
  On 16 March, the IAEA denounced Korea for having rejected 
the 
IAEA specialists' [words indistinct] inspection of nuclear 
facilities. Using this as an excuse, the United States later 
declared that it would cancel the 21 March DPRK-U.S. high-level 
talks. The ROK and the United States are reportedly holding 
negotiations on the Team Spirit joint military exercise. 

</TEXT>

