<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Meets Former Thai Prime Minister Panyarachun </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603125994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1243 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1603125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 16 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice Premier 
Zou Jiahua met here this evening with Anand Panyarachun, former 
prime minister of Thailand, and his party. 
  Zou noted that Sino-Thai relations in every field have been 
good, adding that China welcomes entrepreneurs from Thailand to 
invest here. 
  He said that with its fast economic growth, China has a 
great 
need for energy supplies, in which its cooperation with foreign 
enterprises will enjoy a broad prospect. 
  Anand, who is now chairman of Thailand's Saha Union, said 
that it was his firm's present and future strategy to engage in 
economic cooperation with China, especially in the field of 
power generation. 
  Saha Union is now discussing with many Chinese cities to 
jointly set up power plants in the country. 

