<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Party Entertains Hong Kong, Macao Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803114194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1314 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1803114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 17 Mar (XINHUA) -- The Revolutionary 
Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang [RCCK] Central Committee 
held a cocktail party today to entertain some of the National 
People's Congress [NPC] deputies and Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference [CPPCC] members from Hong Kong and Macao 
attending the two sessions [the Second Sessions of the Eighth 
NPC and Eighth CPPCC National Committee] in Beijing. 
  RCCK Central Committee Chairman Li Peiyao proposed a toast, 
and said: Promoting the motherland's peaceful reunification is 
a major task of the RCCK. In recent years, the RCCK has been 
widely supported for its work in this respect. Within this 
century, China will resume its sovereignty over Hong Kong and 
Macao, and the Taiwan issue will also be placed more urgently in 
front of the people. The RCCK is willing to join hands with 
various sectors and jointly contribute toward the great cause in 
the reversion of Hong Kong and Macao to the motherland as well 
as the peaceful reunification of the two sides of the Taiwan 
Strait. 
  At the party, people from Hong Kong and Macao held cordial 
conversations as well as renewed their friendships with leading 
comrades of the RCCK Central Committee. In addition, they 
exchanged views on many issues. In an enthusiastic atmosphere, 
the hosts and guests frequently raised their glasses to toast 
for the motherland's prosperity and the people's progress. 

</TEXT>

