<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   CPPCC Holds Third Plenary Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703115794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0333 
GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1703115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Zou Aiguo (6760 1947 0948) and Jia Fenyong </F>
(6328 1164 0516)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 16 Mar (XINHUA) -- The Second Session of 
the Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference [CPPCC] held its third plenary meeting 
at the Great Hall of the People this morning. Ten CPPCC members 
took the floor to give their views on the country's major 
policies. 
  Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, 
chaired 
today's meeting. 
  Yang Rudai, Zhao Puchu, and An Zijie served as executive 
chairmen at today's meeting. Wen Jiabao, alternate member of 
the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau and member of the 
Secretariat; State Councillor Peng Peiyun; and comrades in 
charge of ministries and commissions under the State Council 
took part in today's meeting. 
  CPPCC member Fang Rongxin was the first to take the floor. 
On behalf of the Chinese Peasants and Workers Democratic Party, 
he called for stepping up efforts to carry out the population 
work to keep up with the development of the socialist market 
economy. He pointed out: To keep up with the development of 
the situation, we must resolve the population issue, and reform 
provides the fundamental solution. We must continue to uphold 
the target responsibility system in managing the population; 
strengthen grass-roots and basic construction in population 
management; perfect the population management network of rural 
townships and villages and urban neighborhood committees; and 
adopt different methods to improve the quality of our population 
to ensure long-term steady economic development. 
  Member Zhu Guangya spoke on behalf of the China Association 
for Science and Technology, appealing to entire society to truly 
respect science. He said: According to survey, the phenomena 
of failure to respect science and talented personnel has become 
a factor obstructing the healthy development of socialist market 
economy and the building of spiritual civilization. This must 
arouse close attention of entire society and leading departments 
at all levels. He hoped that China's legal system would depend 
on and respect science; provide legal guarantee for scientists 
and technicians who publicize science, and popularize scientific 
knowledge, and bring fake and shoddy products and false 
advertisements into light so as to further develop the social 
trend of "respecting knowledge and professionally trained 
personnel." 
  On behalf of the Central Committee of the Revolutionary 
Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, member Li Ganliu offered a 
suggestion to Taiwan's Kuomintang: The best policy is to quit 
fantasizing, face the reality, change attitude, and sincerely 
accept the CPC's proposal, agree to conduct "three exchanges" 
with China, and hold talks with the CPC as early as possible. 
He said: As long as we reach a consensus on reunification of 
the motherland, can we resolve any problems by negotiations. He 
hoped that Taiwan's Kuomintang would give careful consideration 
to this suggestion, thus making decisions conducive to the 
nation, bringing about a bright future for Taiwan people, and 
writing a new chapter for our history. 
  On behalf of the Central Committee of the China Democratic 
League, member Jiang Jingbo spoke on strengthening democratic 
supervision, and bringing into full play the role of democratic 
parties in socialist democratic political construction. He 
said: Democratic parties in China share the glorious history of 
fighting side by side with the CPC. They also share the common 
object of struggle under the new historical period. As a 
result, a solid ideological and political foundation for the 
CPC-led multiparty cooperation system has thus been established. 
Cooperation implies supervision. We believed that the 
democratic supervision role of democratic parties would be 
brought into full play and China's socialist democratic 
political construction would continue to develop through 
perfecting the CPC-led multiparty cooperation and political 
consultative system. 
  At today's plenary meeting, committee members, including Sun 
Han, Li Yongchang, Jin Xin, Qu Shijing, He Shengtao, and Li 
Zhensheng, spoke on strengthening cooperative economy in rural 
areas, on quickening agricultural development, on conducting 
publicity and education in Marxist view on nationality, on 
developing social sciences, on putting an end to the 
deterioration of our environment, and on popularizing 
agrotechnology. 
  Chairmen of the CPPCC National Committee Ye Xuanping, Wu 
Xueqian, Wang Zhaoguo, Hong Xuezhi, Qian Weichang, Hu Sheng, 
Qian Zhengying, Ding Guangxun, Dong Yinchu, and Sun Fuling 
attended the plenary meeting. 

</TEXT>

