<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   CPPCC Standing Committee Approves Draft Resolutions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803092394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0819 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1803092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 18 (XINHUA) -- The Standing Committee 
of the Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) approved draft 
resolutions and lists of candidates for some new CPPCC leaders 
at its sixth meeting held here this morning. 
  The resolutions and the lists for candidates for 
vice-chairmen, Standing Committee members and secretary-general 
of CPPCC National Committee will be put to a vote at the closing 
meeting of the second session of the CPPCC National Committee 
tomorrow. 
  Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, 
presided over today's meeting. Vice-Chairman Wang Zhaoguo 
briefed participants on discussions of the CPPCC National 
Committee members. 
  He said that the members basically approved the draft 
amendment of the Constitution of the CPPCC and proposed some 
revisions on it. The members expressed satisfaction about all 
draft resolutions. 
  Wang said that the members expressed their appreciation of 
the government work report delivered by Chinese Premier Li Peng 
to the current session of the National People's Congress, saying 
it sums up last year's achievements and experience and outlines 
this year's principles and work. 
  The CPPCC members also raised some suggestions on the report 
concerning price rise control, state-owned large and 
medium-sized enterprises, anti-corruption campaign, agriculture 
and social ethical progress. 
  The meeting also approved the draft political resolution of 
the second session of the CPPCC National Committee and a draft 
resolution on the work report of the standing committee of the 
CPPCC National Committee. 
  At today's meeting participants also examined and approved a 
report by the subcommittee for handling proposals of the CPPCC 
National Committee on examination of the proposals raised by the 
current session of the CPPCC National Committee. 

</TEXT>

