<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Merchandise Sector `Gaining Momentum' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703062594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0609 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703062594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, March 17 (XINHUA) -- China's general 
merchandise sector, both retail and wholesale, is gaining 
momentum, according to a symposium held here recently. 
  Managers who took part in the annual meeting on general 
merchandise, which closed here few days ago, said they believed 
that competition in the market will become more intense. As a 
result, the companies engaged in retail and wholesale will have 
to adjust their business structures and change their management 
mechanisms. 
  Over the past few years many of the state-owned wholesale 
companies in Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai and Guangzhou have made 
great achievements in broadening their business scopes and 
shifting their management mechanisms, according to the meeting. 
  Among the more than 300 members of the national general 
merchandise association, 46 retail and wholesale companies have 
so far adopted the joint stock system, and 16 have been listed 
on the country's stock exchanges. 

</TEXT>

