<H3> <TI>   Beijing's Fifth County-Level TV Station Begins Broadcasting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403024094 Beijing BEIJING RIBAO in Chinese 8 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403024094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing BEIJING RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Gao Deshu (7559 1795 3412), reporter, and Wang Zhigang </F>
(3769 1807 0474), correspondent of the Tongxian County 
reporters' station: "Tongzhou Television Station Begins 
Broadcasting"] 
  [Text] The Beijing Tongzhou Television Station officially 
began broadcasting at 1825 on 6 February in order to provide the 
people in urban and rural areas of Tongxian County to have a 
harmonious and happy Spring Festival. 
  The Beijing Tongzhou Television Station is Beijing's fifth 
county-level (district-level) television station approved by the 
Ministry of Radio, Film, and Television. Its construction, 
which took one year, has provided people the luck to watch more 
television programs. 

</TEXT>

