<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tianjin Establishes Federation of Returned Students </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403042694 Tianjin TIANJIN RIBAO in Chinese 8 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403042694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tianjin TIANJIN RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Tianjin Municipal Federation of Returned 
Students which aims at uniting students who studied abroad, 
extensively connecting domestic and overseas students, 
colleagues, relatives, and friends, strengthening friendship, 
exchanging learning, providing information and service for 
Tianjin to attract students studying abroad, and promoting the 
development of Tianjin's economic construction, science and 
technology, education and public health, culture and sports, and 
other social undertakings, was established yesterday. 
  Gao Dezhan, secretary of the municipal party committee, 
attended and addressed the inaugural meeting. 
  Li Jianguo, deputy secretary of the municipal party 
committee, gave a speech on behalf of the municipal party 
committee and government. 
  Municipal leading persons, including Wang Hongjiang, Wang 
Chenghuai, Qian Qiao, Yu Guocong, and Wang Jitao, attended the 
inaugural meeting. 
  Prior to the inaugural meeting, the Tianjin Municipal 
Federation of Returned Students held a meeting of the board of 
directors to elect Yu Guocong, vice chairman of the municipal 
committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference and member of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, as 
chairman of the federation. It also elected the hnorary 
chairman, advisers, vice chairmen, and secretary general. This 
federation is an organization to unite Tianjin's returned 
students from all circles. [passage omitted] 
  In his speech, Gao Dezhan said: Returning students have made 
great contributions to Tianjin's reform, opening up, and 
economic construction with great patriotic zeal, intelligence, 
and wisdom. They are worthy of emulation. He ardently hoped 
that the broad masses of returned students will give further 
play to their own distinctive advantages, extensively contact 
and attract more overseas students, colleagues, relatives, and 
friends to return to China and Tianjin to work, and to introduce 
trained personnel, funds, and information to promote Tianjin's 
modernization. He said: The broad masses of intellectuals, 
including the returned students, and all sectors across the 
municipality will surely be able to invigorate Tianjin as long 
as they rally around the party Central Committee with Comrade 
Jiang Zemin as the nucleus, act closely in connection with the 
party's overall situation of "seizing the opportunity, deepening 
reform, expanding opening up, promoting development, and 
maintaining stability," work with one heart and one mind, 
struggle in unity, and immerse in hard work. The municipal 
party committee and the government will continue to create an 
external environment in which returned students can display 
their intelligence and wisdom and make contributions, will 
continue to earnestly ask for advice from them, and make joint 
efforts to manage Tianjin's work well. 
  In his speech, Li Jianguo extended warm congratulations to 
the federation of returned students on its establishment on 
behalf of the municipal party committee and government. He 
said: Since the founding of China nearly 45 years ago, batches 
of students studying abroad have returned to the motherland and 
Tianjin to participate in the development and played a very 
important role in Tianjin's economy, science and technology, 
education, public health, and various undertakings. Their pure 
heart of cherishing and serving the motherland and their lofty 
spirit of dedicating themselves to science and invigorating 
China have been praised by the party and the people. 
  Li Jianguo said: Tianjin has several hundred thousand 
specialized technical personnel and a group of specialists and 
scholars who have great influence at home and abroad. This 
backbone contingent is Tianjin's precious wealth and great 
advantage and a symbol of Tianjin's status. We must grasp the 
limited time before the end of this century, step up efforts to 
train a new generation of academic and technical leaders and a 
batch of young top personnel of domestic first-grade level and 
international advanced level, and enable Tianjin to continuously 
maintain the advantage of having trained personnel at home by 
the early period of the next century. 
  Li Jianguo said in conclusion: To push the economy forward, 
we must rely on science, technology, and education and give full 
play to the enthusiasm and creativity of the broad masses of 
intellectuals. We must do a good job in handling work regarding 
returned students. It is hoped that the establishment of the 
Tianjin Municipal Federation of Returned Students will serve as 
a bridge for establishing ties and strengthening friendship with 
the broad masses of returned students, exchanging learning, and 
promoting Tianjin's economic and social development. 

</TEXT>

