<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Macao Holds Tangshan Export Commodities Fair </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703115994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1122 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1703115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, March 17 (XINHUA) -- Tangshan city of north 
China's Hebei Province opened a seven-day export commodities 
fair here this afternoon. 
  It is the first time that the city has conducted such a 
large- scale trade fair overseas. 
  The city's trade delegation brought to the fair more than 
200 
varieties of commodities including foodstuffs, local products, 
hardware, mineral products, chemicals, medicines, machinery and 
equipment, textile, clothes, arts and crafts and pottery and 
porcelain products. They also brought over 300 economic and 
technical cooperative programs covering machinery, chemistry, 
light industry, building materials and porcelain. 
  As an important industrial city in north China, Tangshan 
reported a total industrial and agricultural output value of 
43.24 billion yuan (five billion U.S. dollars) in 1993 and 
recorded 26.4 billion yuan (three billion U.S. dollars) in terms 
of gross domestic product and 330 million U.S. dollars in export 
earnings. 
  At present, the city has more than 3,500 industrial 
enterprises producing over 1,400 varieties of products, some 350 
kinds of products are exported to more than 90 countries and 
regions worldwide. 
  Boasting more than 20 trade companies and a dozen of 
industrial enterprises which have the right to manage their own 
export and import business, Tangshan now has set up trade 
relations with more than 100 countries and regions worldwide. 
Its export commodities include coal, rolled steel, cement, 
porcelain, corn, peanut and Chinese chestnut. 

</TEXT>

