<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Artificial Island for Macao Airport Completed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803092294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0825 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1803092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, March 18 (XINHUA) -- A ceremony marking the 
completion of the artificial island of the Macao International 
Airport was held here today. 
  Costing 5.238 billion Macao patacas (680 million U.S. 
dollars), the artificial island project was signed on January 
18, 1992 and its construction started on March 18 the same year. 
  The 1.5 square kilometer island was built by erecting closed 
dams in the sea and then filling them with sand and stones. 
  The runway of the Macao Airport will be built on the 
artificial island, which was designed to be 3,500 meters long 
and 60 meters wide, and to accommodate B747-400 passenger planes. 
  It was learned that the infrastructural construction in the 
runway area will be started in may this year and is expected to 
be completed in March next year. 
  The surface project of the runway is also expected to be 
finished ahead of schedule to ensure the test flight in next 
June. 
  The Macao International Airport is located at the sea area 
to 
the east of Macao's Taipa and Coloane Islands. With an 
investment of 7.3 billion Macao patacas (940 million U.S. 
dollars), the project was first started in December 1989. The 
airport covers 192 hectares in area. 

</TEXT>

