<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing Court Sentences Three Economic Criminals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0403023494 Beijing BEIJING RIBAO in Chinese 8 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK0403023494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing BEIJING RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the struggle against corruption, the Beijing 
Municipal Intermediate People's Court has persisted in sternly 
cracking down on serious economic criminals. On 7 February, it 
meted out punishments to three economic criminals in the first 
trial. Full-time researcher of the steel rolling institute of 
the Shoudu Iron and Steel Complex, Yang Liyu, was sentenced to 
death with a two-year reprieve and without political rights for 
life on the charge of taking bribes. Zhao Dongxiang, 
commissioner of the raw material section of the Beijing Steel 
Company of the Shoudu Iron and Steel Complex, was sentenced to 
15 years of imprisonment with political rights deprived for 
three years for taking bribes. Wang Ning, director of the 
finance section of the Beijing No. 10 Radio Component Plant, was 
sentenced to death with a two-year reprieve and had his 
political rights taken away for life for bribe-taking, 
embezzlement, and misuse of public funds. 

</TEXT>

